## 7. Common Pitfalls and Best Practices

### ❌ Pitfall 1: Unsigned Loop with >= 0

```c
for (unsigned short u = 10; u >= 0; u--);  // ❌ Infinite loop
```

### ✅ Solution

```c
for (unsigned short u = 10; u > 0; u--);   // ✅ Terminates at u = 0
// or use signed short
```

---

### ❌ Pitfall 2: Mixing Signed and Unsigned in Comparisons

```c
signed short a = -1;
unsigned short b = 1;
if (a < b) {  // ❌ Unexpected: a promoted to unsigned (65535)
    printf("True");
}
```

### ✅ Solution

```c
// Cast to same type for comparison
if ((short)a < (short)b) {  // ✅ Both signed
    printf("True");
}
```

---

### ❌ Pitfall 3: Overflow Without Awareness

```c
short s = 32767;
s++;  // ❌ Overflows to -32768 without warning
```

### ✅ Solution

```c
short s = 32767;
if (s < 32767) {  // ✅ Check before incrementing
    s++;
} else {
    printf("Overflow prevented\n");
}
```

